        <p style="padding-left:30px;"><span style="font-weight:400;">We were 15 minutes into our newfound friendship, and the nerves were long gone.  We were a bunch of sisters!  Singing, laughing, crying, sharing stories&#8230;  It was hard to get the attention of the room as everyone was so eager to get to know one another, but I had one more activity in store.  In the spirit of our program, “Phenomenal Woman,” we went around the room and introduced ourselves, naming the Phenomenal Women in our lives.  Many women called forth names of their mothers or grandmothers, sisters, children, or even other women in the room.  I don’t think I was alone in feeling both incredibly vulnerable and incredibly powerful.  And what fertile ground for music to enter in, take seed, and grow. </span>
